<br>
Celtic Dual does the same when BOTH weapons swing.  Otherwise, the delay is calculated based on the one weapon swung.<br>
<br>
For example - let's say I am wielding a 3.6 spd Guarded Rapier, and a 2.2 spd Dirk.<br>
<br>
Round A:  I swing both the rapier and the dirk.  The delay to my next attack will be (3.6 + 2.2)/2<br>
<br>
Round B: I swing only the rapier.  The delay to the next attack will be 3.6 s.<br>
<br>
Round C: I swing only the dirk.  The delay to the next attack will be 2.2 s. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chojin@lighttanksofdaoc>CHOJIN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#000000>(3/22/03 4:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ?¿</span><hr size=1> mhh.. so it is better to wear a slow mainhand and a fast offhand like the la users do? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shanahankilbeggin>Shanahan Kilbeggin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#000000>(3/22/03 7:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?¿</span><hr size=1> If you're a gambling man, yes. <p>=======<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotherald.com/realms/Kay/">Hibernia/Kay</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> – <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.pk-hq.com/community/forumdisplay.php?s=&amp;forumid=185">Storm's Fury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->=======<br>
