This is because, when you can style constantly, you'll either always swing at the speed of the faster weapon, or at the average of the two.  You'll never be stuck with the slower off hand speed, but you will sometimes pick up extra off hand damage for a smaller delay penalty. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stryhf>Stryhf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(4/7/03 8:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mhh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
If that formula is correct, then in situations where you'll have end song, you're best off using a slow OFF hand weapon, and a faster main hand weapon.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Only in cases of PVE.  The issue arises in RvR where you want to maximize your Front Loaded Damage.  Style damage always takes into account your primary hand.  The &quot;benefit&quot; of Left Axe is that a fast fast offhand will speed up their primary hand, while they maintain maximum style damage.<br>
<br>
Left Axe starts weak and has a linear growth rate (each spec in Left Axe returns exactly the same return, statistically)<br>
Duel Wield and CDW starts with a decent percent, and possesses an inversely geometric growth rate (return on spec stabilizes and reduces past 20).<br>
<br>
Using a slower offhand while styling all the time almost seems counterintuitive.  You're trading off delay for base DPS, while losing in style damage (style damage is sorely based upon your primary hand's delay).<br>
